        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "Now that both `df_all_ceos` and `df_stocks` DataFrames are prepared with common `date` and `company` columns, I will merge them using an inner join to combine tweet sentiment data with corresponding daily stock data, as specified in the subtask.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cc0d617b"
      },
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure 'date' column in df_all_ceos is of type date for consistent merging\n",
        "df_all_ceos['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_all_ceos['created_at']).dt.date\n",
        "\n",
        "# Merge df_all_ceos and df_stocks on 'date' and 'company'\n",
        "# Using an inner merge to only keep rows where both tweet and stock data exist for a given date and company.\n",
        "df_merged = pd.merge(\n",
        "    df_all_ceos,\n",
        "    df_stocks[['date', 'company', 'open', 'high', 'low', 'close', 'volume']], # Select relevant stock columns\n",
        "    on=['date', 'company'],\n",
        "    how='inner'\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Merged DataFrame (df_merged) created:\")\n",
        "display(df_merged.head())"
